  <refnamediv>
    <refname>detcoef</refname>
    <refpurpose>1-D detail coefficients extraction</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>D :</term>
            <listitem><para> reconstructed detail coefficient</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>C :</term>
            <listitem><para> coefficent array</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>L :</term>
            <listitem><para> length array</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>N :</term>
            <listitem><para> restruction level with N&lt;=length(L)-2</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
detcoef is for extraction of detail coeffient at different level
after a multiple level decompostion. Extension mode is stored as
a global variable and could be changed with dwtmode. If N is omitted,
the detail coefficients will extract at the  maximum level (length(L)-2).
   </para>
   <para>
The length of D depends on the level N.
   </para>
   <para>
C and L can be generated using wavedec.
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
X = wnoise(4,10,0.5); //doppler with N=1024
[C,L]=wavedec(X,3,'db2');
D2=detcoef(C,L,2);
scf();clf();
subplot(211);
plot(X,'r');
subplot(212);
plot(D2);
   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

